  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The governing requirement mandates a controlled-experiment verification approach; the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study drawing on registry and clinical surveillance data, which the narrative presents as functionally equivalent. The structured activityType field, however, records 'observational-study', creating an inference-method mismatch with the requirement's requiredVerificationMethod of 'controlled-experiment'.",
