    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required Gradation 2 levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. The validation activity against the multi-centre clinical registry demonstrates agreement within the ±15% RHI acceptance criterion across all five operating points (Pearson r = 0.94), providing high confidence in the CFD model's ability to identify worst-case hemolysis conditions for the Class II CPB device. The credibility assessment team concludes that the model is fit for the stated context of use and the submission is accepted.",
